==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fng-shui
<hw>F⟦ecir⟧ng"-shu`i</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Chin.
<ets>feng</ets> wind + <ets>shiu</ets> water.]</ety> <def>A system of
spirit influences for good and evil believed by the Chinese to attend
the natural features of landscape; also, a kind of geomancy dealing with
these influences, used in determining sites for graves, houses,
etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fenian</ent>⟦br⟧
